The Biden-Harris Administration recently held a meeting with representatives from manufacturers, manufacturing experts, and manufacturers' associations to discuss how small and medium-sized domestic manufacturers can participate in the Investing in America agenda. The meeting included officials such as Lael Brainard, Mitch Landrieu, and Heather Boushey, who reviewed opportunities for domestic manufacturers in clean energy, infrastructure, and semi-conductor supply chains. The Administration highlighted how their investments in American infrastructure and clean energy are revitalizing the manufacturing base, promoting innovation, and creating high-quality jobs. They also discussed the importance of supporting training and education for manufacturers to find the skilled workforce they need. The manufacturers provided advice on how the Biden-Harris Administration can better reach small firms and help them capitalize on the opportunities in Investing in America supply chains.